    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Hands-on_Ex05_Building_Ternary_PlotWR\"\nformat: html\nauthor: \"Persis Evangeline\"\ndate: \"May 15, 2026\"\ndate-modified: \"last-modified\"\nexecute: \n  eval: true\n  echo: true\n  warning: false\n  freeze: true\n---\nA ternary plot is a special type of graph used to visualise compositional data made up of 3 parts that together sum to a constant.This constant is usually 1 or 100%. Some examples include population groups (young, economically active, elderly), soil composition(sand, clay, silt) and budget allocation( savings, expenses, investments). Each corner of the triangle represents 100% of 1 component and 0% of the other 2 components.   \n\n# Getting Started\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\npacman::p_load(plotly, ggtern, tidyverse)\n```\n:::\n\n# Importing Dataset\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\npop_data <- read.csv(\"respopagsex2000to2018_tidy.csv\")\n```\n:::\n\n\n# Preparing data\n\nUtilising mutate() function  \n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\n# Deriving the young, economy active and old measures\n\nagpop_mutated <- pop_data %>% \n  mutate(`Year` = as.character(Year))%>%\n  spread(AG, Population) %>%\n  mutate(YOUNG = rowSums(.[4:8])) %>%\n  mutate(ACTIVE = rowSums(.[9:16])) %>%\n  mutate(OLD = rowSums(.[17:21])) %>%\n  mutate(TOTAL = rowSums(.[22:24])) %>%\n  filter(Year == 2018) %>%\n  filter(TOTAL >0)\n```\n:::\n\n\n# Plotting Ternary diagram with R\n\n::: panel-tabset\n## The plot\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](Hands-on_Ex05_Building_Ternary_PlotWR_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-4-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n:::\n\n## The code\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\n#Building the static ternary plot\nggtern(data=agpop_mutated,aes(x=YOUNG,y=ACTIVE, z=OLD)) +\n  geom_point()\n```\n:::\n\n:::\n\n\n# Building the static ternary plot\n\n::: panel-tabset\n## The plot\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](Hands-on_Ex05_Building_Ternary_PlotWR_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-6-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n:::\n\n## The code\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nggtern(data=agpop_mutated, aes(x=YOUNG,y=ACTIVE, z=OLD)) +\n  geom_point() +\n  labs(title=\"Population structure, 2015\") +\n  theme_rgbw()\n```\n:::\n\n:::\n\n# Plotting an interactive ternary diagram\n\n::: panel-tabset\n## The plot\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"plotly html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-d1bf402a9737044738b1\" style=\"width:100%;height:464px;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-d1bf402a9737044738b1\">{\"x\":{\"visdat\":{\"cac69201bb8\":[\"function () \",\"plotlyVisDat\"]},\"cur_data\":\"cac69201bb8\",\"attrs\":{\"cac69201bb8\":{\"a\":{},\"b\":{},\"c\":{},\"color\":[\"black\"],\"alpha_stroke\":1,\"sizes\":[10,100],\"spans\":[1,20],\"type\":\"scatterternary\"}},\"layout\":{\"margin\":{\"b\":40,\"l\":60,\"t\":25,\"r\":10},\"annotations\":[{\"text\":\"Ternary Markers\",\"x\":0.10000000000000001,\"y\":1,\"ax\":0,\"ay\":0,\"xref\":\"paper\",\"yref\":\"paper\",\"align\":\"center\",\"font\":{\"family\":\"serif\",\"size\":15,\"color\":\"white\"},\"bgcolor\":\"#b3b3b3\",\"bordercolor\":\"black\",\"borderwidth\":2},{\"text\":\"Ternary Markers\",\"x\":0.10000000000000001,\"y\":1,\"ax\":0,\"ay\":0,\"xref\":\"paper\",\"yref\":\"paper\",\"align\":\"center\",\"font\":{\"family\":\"serif\",\"size\":15,\"color\":\"white\"},\"bgcolor\":\"#b3b3b3\",\"bordercolor\":\"black\",\"borderwidth\":2},{\"text\":\"Ternary Markers\",\"x\":0.10000000000000001,\"y\":1,\"ax\":0,\"ay\":0,\"xref\":\"paper\",\"yref\":\"paper\",\"align\":\"center\",\"font\":{\"family\":\"serif\",\"size\":15,\"color\":\"white\"},\"bgcolor\":\"#b3b3b3\",\"bordercolor\":\"black\",\"borderwidth\":2}],\"ternary\":{\"aaxis\":{\"title\":\"Young\",\"tickformat\":\".0%\",\"tickfont\":{\"size\":10}},\"baxis\":{\"title\":\"Active\",\"tickformat\":\".0%\",\"tickfont\":{\"size\":10}},\"caxis\":{\"title\":\"Old\",\"tickformat\":\".0%\",\"tickfont\":{\"size\