\n\n:::\n:::\n\n## The code\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nlibrary(plotly)\n\nplot_ly(\n  data = agpop_mutated,\n\n  a = ~YOUNG,\n  b = ~ACTIVE,\n  c = ~OLD,\n\n  type = \"scatterternary\",\n  mode = \"markers\",\n\n  text = ~paste(\n    \"Planning Area:\", PA,\n    \"<br>Young:\", YOUNG,\n    \"<br>Active:\", ACTIVE,\n    \"<br>Old:\", OLD,\n    \"<br>Total:\", TOTAL\n  ),\n\n  hoverinfo = \"text\",\n\n  marker = list(\n    size = 8,\n    color = \"darkred\"\n  )\n\n) %>%\n\n  layout(\n    title = \"Interactive Population Ternary Plot\",\n\n    margin = list(\n      t = 100,\n      l = 50,\n      r = 50,\n      b = 50\n    ),\n\n    ternary = list(\n      aaxis = list(title = \"Young\"),\n      baxis = list(title = \"Active\"),\n      caxis = list(title = \"Old\")\n    )\n  )\n```\n:::\n\n:::",
